A panel of Indian bureaucrats
recommended allowing foreign companies to own up to 51 percent
in multi-brand retail stores, according to a finance ministry
official with direct knowledge of the matter.  The panel has proposed a minimum investment of $100 million
by overseas retailers in the worldâ€™s second-most populous
country, the official said, requesting not to be identified
before a public announcement. The cabinet will take a final
